				<div id="content">
					<div class="panel">
						<div class="portlet">
							<h1>Before and After Restoration Pictures</h1>
							<p>Click on the photographs to view a larger image.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="portlet">
							<h2>Marshall &amp; Rose Piano</h2>
							<p>
								<a class="lightbox" href="/static/images/internal/large/marshalrosebefore.jpg" title="Marshal Rose Before Restoration">
									<img class="si" src="/static/images/internal/marshalrosebefore.jpg" width="100" height="75" alt="Marshal Rose Before Restoration"/></a>
								<a class="lightbox" href="/static/images/internal/large/marshalroseafter.jpg" title="Marshal Rose After Restoration">
									<img class="si" src="/static/images/internal/marshalroseafter.jpg" width="100" height="75" alt="Marshal Rose After Restoration"/></a>
								This rosewood piano went through the full repolishing process. On arrival at the shop the case was considerably worn and marked, and very much in need of some attention.
								The satin finish flatters the piano and brings the case back to life.
							</p>

						</div>
						<div class="portlet">
							<h2>Steck Grand Piano</h2>
							<p>
								<a class="lightbox" href="/static/images/internal/large/steckbefore.jpg" title="Steck Before Restoration">
									<img class="si" src="/static/images/internal/steckbefore.jpg" width="100" height="75" alt="Steck Before Restoration"/></a>
								<a class="lightbox" href="/static/images/internal/large/steckafter.jpg" title="Steck After Restoration">
									<img class="si" src="/static/images/internal/steckafter.jpg" width="100" height="75" alt="Steck After Restoration"/></a>
								This Steck grand piano also underwent a full case restoration. The original polish was dull, with surface cracks, scratches and dents. A total strip down and repolish
								in a satin mahogany finish brings out the beauty of the wood.
							</p>
						</div>

						<div class="portlet">
							<h2>Kaps Upright Piano</h2>
							<p>
								<a class="lightbox" href="/static/images/internal/large/kapsbefore.jpg" title="Kaps Before Restoration">
									<img class="si" src="/static/images/internal/kapsbefore.jpg" width="100" height="75" alt="Kaps Before Restoration"/></a>
								<a class="lightbox" href="/static/images/internal/large/kapsafter.jpg" title="Kaps After Restoration">
									<img class="si" src="/static/images/internal/kapsafter.jpg" width="100" height="75" alt="Kaps After Restoration"/></a>
								Another example of how repolishing can transform a piano. Once again, the old polish does nothing to fulfil the potential of this Kaps piano. The new finish
								brings out the colour and grain of the wood, set off perfectly by the brass inlay.
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="portlet">
							<h2>Grand Piano Frame</h2>
							<p>
								<a class="lightbox" href="/static/images/internal/large/framebefore.jpg" title="Frame Before Restoration">
									<img class="si" src="/static/images/internal/framebefore.jpg" width="100" height="75" alt="Frame Before Restoration"/></a>
								<a class="lightbox" href="/static/images/internal/large/frameafter.jpg" title="Frame After Restoration">
									<img class="si" src="/static/images/internal/frameafter.jpg" width="100" height="75" alt="Frame After Restoration"/></a>
								This shows the results of a repolished soundboard and resprayed frame. Before restoration, the gold paint has faded, and dirt is ingrained in all the parts.
								The frame is totally removed and resprayed, whilst the soundboard is repaired, sanded and repolished.
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="portlet">
							<h2>Piano Action</h2>

							<p>
								<a class="lightbox" href="/static/images/internal/large/actionbefore.jpg" title="Action Before Restoration">
									<img class="si" src="/static/images/internal/actionbefore.jpg" width="100" height="75" alt="Action Before Restoration"/></a>
								<a class="lightbox" href="/static/images/internal/large/actionafter.jpg" title="Action After Restoration">
									<img class="si" src="/static/images/internal/actionafter.jpg" width="100" height="75" alt="Action After Restoration"/></a>
								These pictures show some of the work done to an upright action. The action has been cleaned out, including the polished brass hammer rest rail. The hammers, damper
								felts and return tapes have all been renewed, careful measurements of the old parts having first been taken.
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="portlet">
							<h2>Pins and Frame</h2>
							<p>

								<a class="lightbox" href="/static/images/internal/large/pinsbefore.jpg" title="Pins Before Restoration">
									<img class="si" src="/static/images/internal/pinsbefore.jpg" width="100" height="75" alt="Pins Before Restoration"/></a>
								<a class="lightbox" href="/static/images/internal/large/pinsafter.jpg" title="Pins After Restoration">
									<img class="si" src="/static/images/internal/pinsafter.jpg" width="100" height="75" alt="Pins After Restoration"/></a>
								These pictures show in detail the complete restoration of a grand piano frame. The frame itself has been resprayed, and new felt attached.
								The piano has also been given brand new strings and tuning pins. Even the frame bolts have been polished up to complete the job.
							</p>
						</div>
